Nixon 57%, Carter 37% (CNN) - Former President Richard Nixon leads former Democratic President Jimmy Carter in the latest CNN/Opinion Research Corp. poll on the 2008 presidential race. The 57% support for Nixon is the highest percentage for a former president since 1965, when 60% of Americans said they would vote for former President Dwight D. Eisenhower. Although the initial arrests took place under the jurisdiction of local D.C. police, the case was soon taken over by the FBI.
